{"ok": true, "lean_translation": "import Mathlib


/-- Let n be a fixed positive integer and let a,b,c be integers. Show that if a ≡ b (mod n) and b ≡ c (mod n), then a ≡ c (mod n). Translate into Lean4 and end the theorem with := by sorry. Import Mathlib at the top and save as a theorem statement. -/
theorem trans_ext : ∀ {n a b c : ℤ}, a ≡ b [ZMOD n] → b ≡ c [ZMOD n] → a ≡ c [ZMOD n] := sorry"}
